    Subject: Mateusz Korbiel, born 04.03.1997, last known address:
             ul. Lipowa 14/3, 30-420 Krakow, Polish national

Dear colleagues,

I represent Mateusz Korbiel as defence counsel in criminal proceedings
before the Landgericht Stuttgart (Higher Regional Court Stuttgart), Germany,
case no. KLs 4 Js 18.422/26.

The Staatsanwaltschaft Stuttgart has filed a legal assistance request
(Rechtshilfeersuchen) with your office on 28 October 2025 (Ref. PO/K/RH-2025-
4471), seeking information on prior convictions and pending proceedings
against my client.

Your office has already provided partial information (letter of 08 January
2026), which I acknowledge with thanks. According to that correspondence,
two prior entries exist:
- SR 2/2019/K (Einbruchdiebstahl / burglary, 2018, Krakow) -- conditional
  sentence 18 months
- SR 14/2022/K (Koerperverletzung / bodily harm, 2021, Krakow) -- fine

SPECIFIC REQUEST (DEFENCE COUNSEL):
As defence counsel, I kindly request the following:

1. Full copy of the judgment in case SR 2/2019/K in German translation
   (or English if German not available), including sentencing reasoning
   (Strafzumessungsgruende). This is required to assess proportionality
   of the German sentence under § 46 Abs. 2 StGB (German Criminal Code).

2. Confirmation whether any additional proceedings against Korbiel are
   pending (besides the already-reported SR 3/2025/K online fraud case).

3. Information on whether Korbiel has fully completed the conditional sentence
   from SR 2/2019/K (probation period expired).

LEGAL BASIS:
This request is made pursuant to the European Convention on Mutual Assistance
in Criminal Matters (EuRhUeB) of 20 April 1959 and the bilateral legal
assistance agreement between Germany and Poland (BGBl 2004 II, 898).

Please note that we intend to use this information in the defence's
sentencing submission (Strafzumessungs-Plaedoyer) in the forthcoming
main hearing (Hauptverhandlung) scheduled for May-June 2026 before the
Landgericht Stuttgart.

We would appreciate a response by 28 February 2026. Please address any
reply to both our office and to the Staatsanwaltschaft Stuttgart
(OStAin K. Freudenberg, cc'd).

With best professional regards,

